Object.Field: LKM Hyperion Financial Management Members To SQL

Author: Sunopsis Version: 4.0 Last update: Oct 17 2007
Description: - Loading Knowledge Module - Loads data from a Hyperion Financial Management Application - This module uses Sunopsis Agent to extract members from a MemberList defined in the Hyperion Financial Management Application and write the result in the target temporary table created dynamically.
Restrictions:
Specifies the name of the dimension for which you are extracting the members. This parameter is required
Flag to indicate if logging should be performed during the load process. If set to Yes, logging would be done to the file specified by the LOG_FILE_NAME option.
The fully qualified name of the file into which logging is to be done.
Specifies the name of the member list. This parameter is required.
Specifies the top member of the member list. The system extracts all the descendants of this top member in the Member List specified by the MEMBER_LIST_NAME option.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.

from java.util import HashMap from java.util import Map from java.lang import Boolean from com.hyperion.odi.common import ODIConstants from com.hyperion.odi.connection import HypAppConnectionFactory from com.hyperion.odi.hfm import ODIHFMAppReader from com.hyperion.odi.hfm import ODIHFMConstants
# # Source HFM Application connection properties #
serverName = "<%=odiRef.getInfo("SRC_DSERV_NAME")%>" userName = "<%=odiRef.getInfo("SRC_USER_NAME")%>" password = "<%=odiRef.getInfo("SRC_PASS")%>" application = "<%=odiRef.getInfo("SRC_CATALOG")%>"
# # Put the connection properites and initialize the HFM App Reader # srcProps = HashMap() srcProps.put(ODIConstants.SERVER,serverName) srcProps.put(ODIConstants.USER,userName) srcProps.put(ODIConstants.PASSWORD,password) srcProps.put(ODIConstants.APPLICATION_NAME,application)
print "Initalizing the HFM App Reader and connecting" hfmAppReader = HypAppConnectionFactory.getAppReader(HypAppConnectionFactory.APP_HFM, srcProps);
connection = odiRef.getJDBCConnection("DEST") print "Established connection to the staging database."
stagingTableName = ' <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "COLL_NAME", "W")%>'
print "Staging table Name is %s" % stagingTableName
stagCols = '<%=odiRef.getColList("", "[CX_COL_NAME]=[COL_NAME] ", ", ", "", "")%>' print "Staging Columns %s" % stagCols # #extract the LKM Options # logEnabled = <%=odiRef.getOption("LOG_ENABLED")%> logFileName = r"<%=odiRef.getOption("LOG_FILE_NAME")%>"
dimensionName = "<%=odiRef.getOption("DIMENSION_NAME")%>" memberListName = "<%=odiRef.getOption("MEMBER_LIST_NAME")%>" topMember = "<%=odiRef.getOption("TOP_MEMBER")%>"
#set the extract options
extractOptions = HashMap()
#generic ODI Knowledge module options extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.LOG_ENABLED, Boolean(logEnabled)) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.LOG_FILE_NAME, logFileName)
#HFM specific load options extractOptions.put(ODIHFMConstants.OPTIONS_NAME_SOURCECONNECTION, connection) extractOptions.put(ODIHFMConstants.OPTIONS_NAME_COLUMNMAP, stagCols) extractOptions.put(ODIHFMConstants.OPTIONS_NAME_TABLENAME,stagingTableName) extractOptions.put(ODIHFMConstants.OPTIONS_NAME_LKM_EXTRACT_LIST_DIM_NAME,dimensionName) extractOptions.put(ODIHFMConstants.OPTIONS_NAME_LKM_EXTRACT_LIST_MEMBER_LIST_NAME,memberListName) extractOptions.put(ODIHFMConstants.OPTIONS_NAME_LKM_EXTRACT_LIST_TOP_MEMBER,topMember) extractOptions.put(ODIHFMConstants.MODEL_TABLETYPE_KEY, ODIHFMConstants.MODEL_TABLETYPE_MEMBERLIST)
hfmAppReader.beginExtract(extractOptions)
statsString=stats.toString() raise "HFM Extract Members Summary: ", statsString
